ng on the move, so that mobility becomes a ubiquitous feature of our lives. This book is a valuable resource to anyone interested in multimodal interaction and mobility.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aBody languagexPsychological aspects. 0aCommunication models. 0aGesture. 0aNonverbal communication. 4aInteraktion. 4aMobilität. 4aMultimodalität. 4aPragmatik. 4aVerkörperung. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Communication Studies.2bisacsh  aSocial interaction.  aembodiment.  alanguage in use.  amobility.  amultimodality.1 aArminen, Ilkka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBroth, Mathias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBüscher, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Stefani, Elwys, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaddington, Pentti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaddington, Pentti, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHemment, Drew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeevallik, Leelo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoskela, Inka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLan Hing Ting, Karine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaurier, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLehn, Dirk vom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLicoppe, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLundström, Fredrik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcIlvenny, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMondada, Lore